[thinking] 
[thinking] Okay, so I’m thinking about the dynamic-class-loading pattern and how it can handle unsupported features. The task specifies that tests should run in a Native environment by default, but unsupported class loading might throw an error. I wonder if I could avoid this issue by generating a class at compile time. Creating a test for just the `getMethods` might be okay, but the task demands more coverage. I’ll also need the library JAR path for the child URLClassLoader.
