[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm trying to figure out whether to load the Scala library from the parent or child class. If the child can't load Scala, that poses a problem. Ideally, I want the child to take precedence for Akka classes, while using the parent for current Scala and JavaX classes. If the parent has Akka classes as well, the default parent-first method will load `Http2` from there, which won't use any custom ALPN settings. This needs careful consideration!
