ary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating mapping issues**\\n\\nI’m checking a potential issue with one-to-one mapping in the dynamic-access report classes and the generated test class files. We only have one file, which is good! I wonder if the generated class `sun.security.ssl.ALPNExtension` can load through the URLClassLoader with the parent app. The `loadClass` override first calls `findClass`, but I need to clarify the parent-child relationship for class loading.\\n\\nI’ve noted that invoking `Http().connectionTo` might pose some issues due to how it's overloaded and how the ActorSystem is implicated. I'll also consider potential conflicts with the Akka HTTP version to ensure everything is functioning correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining exception handling**\\n\\nI'm considering that an exception might be thrown during flow materialization, not just as a stream failure. This means that if `system.terminate` is in the `finally` block, it may never execute. I should wrap the operation in a try-catch to ensure that the `finally` block runs correctly.\\n\\nIf `requestFailure` comes from materializing and throws an exception instead of returning a failure, I'll need to skip the assert and jump straight to the `finally` block. It looks like the `InvocationTargetException` could be the root cause being a RuntimeException.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DE3Q5U9GajKvCUovt5byR3e9|fc_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb1376d8d4819697bd0babdfc9f201", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git status --short"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 664, "output": 893, "cacheRead": 46080, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47637, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778062181852, "responseId": "resp_06ca1d19fe6b72bd0169fb13694cb88196ae66f2d0f3437d95"}}
