[assistant] 
[assistant] - Added `tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-http-core_2.13/10.5.3/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_http_core_2_13/Http2AlpnSupportTest.scala`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What it covers:
[assistant] - Forces the JDK-8 ALPN compatibility branch by setting `java.specification.version` to `1.8` before loading Akka HTTP in an isolated child-first class loader.
[assistant] - Provides a controlled `sun.security.ssl.ALPNExtension` class to make Akka HTTP execute the legacy Jetty ALPN detection path.
[assistant] - Exercises the public HTTP/2 client API (`Http().connectionTo(...).http2()`), reaching:
[assistant]   - `Class#getMethods()` in `Http2AlpnSupport$.isAlpnSupportedByJDK`
[assistant]   - `Class#getDeclaredMethods()` in the Jetty ALPN detection lambda
[assistant] - Uses a bounded wait and terminates the `ActorSystem`.
[assistant] - Handles Native Image unsupported dynamic class loading via `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run tests, per instruction.
